vocabInfos.mediumDef:
A man living at the time before the Flood, first mentioned at Gen.5.9;
son of: Enosh (H0583);
father of: Mahalalel (H4111); also called Cainan at Luk.3.37;
Also named: Kainan, Kainam<\i> (Καϊνάν, Καϊνάμ "Cainan" G2536H)
§ Kenan = "possession"
1) son of Enosh and father of Mahalaleel
1a) also 'Cainan'
vocabInfos._es_Definition: hijo de Enós; descendiente de Set
vocabInfos._zh_tw_Definition:
該南 这个陽性專有名詞 人名在原文的意思是 "擁有"
以挪士的兒子, 瑪勒列的父親
vocabInfos._zh_Definition:
该南 这个阳性专有名词 人名在原文的意思是 "拥有"
以挪士的儿子, 玛勒列的父亲
